{
  "texts": [
    "Die-to-wafer bonding provides the flexibility of using known-good dies, increasing yield.",
    "Wafer-to-wafer bonding remains expensive because the size mismatches between the SOI acceptor wafers (200 mm or 300 mm) and the modulator donor wafers (150 mm or smaller) lead to wastage.",
    "Integration proximity of the (dissimilar) materials in direct bonding facilitates superior optical coupling and heat transportation between them 56.",
    "However, very smooth and clean surfaces are required.",
    "Chemical mechanical polishing (CMP) procedures, already used in high-volume manufacturing (HVM) for heterogeneous direct bonding of InP to Si for lasers, must be optimized for a scalable modulator integration pathway."
  ]
}